oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Pre-Columbian Panamanian ceramic vessel with applique decoration
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pre-Columbian vessel with a rounded base and a red ochre slip. An oval appliqué incised with a horizontal line projects from the shoulder. There is evidence of a protrusion from the vessel's lip and body, although it is unclear what its function was.
Protrusions on the lip and body are broken.
